simj

Class SimEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • simj.SimEvent
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    EvenementNouveauClient, EvenementNouvelleMachine, SimEventResource, SimEventScanResources

    public abstract class SimEvent
extends Object
    This class implements the generic concept of a discrete event. The management of the event firing is implemented, but the abstract execute feature must be implemented.
    Author:
    Patrik Fuhrer

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        public abstract void execute()
        Does the actual work of this event. This is a primitive operation and each concrete event has to implement it appropriately.

      • getCurrentTime

        protected final double getCurrentTime()
        Returns the current time of the simulation. This commoditiy method is useful for subclasses.
        Returns:
        The current time of the simulation.

        Returns:

      • schedule

        protected final void schedule(double pFiringTime)
        Schedules this event at a given time. This visibility of this method is protected to allow subclasses to reschedule themselves if needed.
        Parameters:
        pFiringTime - The firing or execution time of this event.
